Elron Software - a provider of spam, email and web filtering solutions, sold to Zix Corp.[6]
Oren Semiconductor - a fabless integrated circuits manufacturer that designs and develops integrated circuits for the digital television and set-top box markets, sold to Zoran Corporation.[7]
Galil Medical - a developer of cryotherapy solutions.[8]
SELA Semiconductor Engineering Laboratories - a provider of automated sample preparation tools for semiconductor manufacturers, sold to Camtek Intelligent Imaging.[8]
3DV Systems - developers of the ZCam, a time-of-flight camera products for video applications, sold to Microsoft.[9]
Medingo - developer of a micro pump insulin delivery system consists of two parts: a semi-disposable insulin dispensing patch and a remote control, which allows for discreet personalised insulin delivery. The company was sold to Hoffmann-La Roche's subsidiary Roche Diagnostics for $160 million as well as up to $40 million in milestone payments.[10]
